"""Test data workflows - dispatcher.

Two separate workflows available:

1. marimo_orig_qgen.smk - Queue generator validation
   Source: qg_20260119_dump/20260119_dump/*.csv (409 B-Fabric queue files)
   Usage: snakemake -s marimo_orig_qgen.smk -j4 all

2. marimo_queue_analysis.smk - Queue analysis from SLD files
   Source: reference/sld/ (SLD binary files from instruments)
   Usage: snakemake -s marimo_queue_analysis.smk -j4 all
"""

rule help:
    """Show available workflows."""
    run:
        print("""
Test Data Workflows
===================

Two separate workflows are available:

1. Queue Generator Validation (from B-Fabric dump)
   ------------------------------------------------
   Source: qg_20260119_dump/20260119_dump/*.csv (409 files)

   Commands:
     snakemake -s marimo_orig_qgen.smk -j4 all        # Full pipeline
     snakemake -s marimo_orig_qgen.smk marimo_app     # Launch viewer
     snakemake -s marimo_orig_qgen.smk clean_all      # Clean up

2. Queue Analysis (from SLD files)
   --------------------------------
   Source: reference/sld/ (SLD binary files)

   Commands:
     snakemake -s marimo_queue_analysis.smk -j4 all   # Full pipeline
     snakemake -s marimo_queue_analysis.smk marimo_app # Launch viewer
     snakemake -s marimo_queue_analysis.smk clean     # Clean up
""")


rule default:
    input: []
    run:
        print("Use 'snakemake help' to see available workflows")
        print("Or run a specific workflow with -s flag:")
        print("  snakemake -s marimo_orig_qgen.smk -j4 all")
        print("  snakemake -s marimo_queue_analysis.smk -j4 all")
